  "description": "Configure GitHub Pages Deployment for Custom Domain Path\n\nUpdate the application configuration to work correctly when deployed to GitHub Pages at the URL path http://bartusiak.ai/wesole_nutki/.\n\nRequirements:\n- Configure base URL/path prefix to handle the /wesole_nutki/ subdirectory\n- Update asset paths (CSS, JavaScript, images) to load from correct location\n- Fix navigation/routing to work with the subdirectory path structure\n- Update any hardcoded URLs or absolute paths to be relative or include base path\n- Ensure all internal links navigate correctly within the subdirectory context\n- Test that all pages, resources, and navigation work correctly at the deployed URL\n- Update build configuration to include proper publicPath or base settings\n- Verify no 404 errors for assets or routes when accessing the site\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Direct navigation to nested routes (e.g., /wesole_nutki/about)\n- Browser refresh on non-root pages\n- Links in dynamically generated content\n- API endpoints or external resource references if applicable",
